noun.description: A person who plays a racket game, especially tennis.

origin: Late 16th century; earliest use found in Richard Mulcaster (?1532–1611), schoolmaster and author. From racket + -er. In later use in sense 1 perhaps partly also from racket + -er<br>mid 17th century. Partly from racket + -er, and partly from racket + -er.
